results.title: Record-Breaking High Temperature in Twin Cities

-MVOto0cYdNrtsCrHevT.text: Incident reported at Minneapolis-St Paul Int'l Airport.

-MVOto4zJVKakh_ZUnf4.text: Minneapolis-St Paul broke a 142-year-old record today when temperatures reached 63°F. The previous record for March 9 was 61°F, recorded in 1879.

nib.text:
The record high temperature for March 9 is 63°F, which was set today at 3:15 p.m., according to the National Weather Service (NWS). The prior record was 61°F, set in 1879. 

Wednesday's forecast is a high of 48°F with a good possibility of rain throughout the day, however snow is unlikely. Temperature highs are expected to fluctuate between the high 40s and low 50s throughout the next week.
